《'''蘇格蘭之花'''》（{{lang-sco|Flouer o Scotland}}；{{lang-en|Flower of Scotland}}；{{lang-gd|Flùr na h-Alba}}）是一首[[苏格兰|苏格兰]]歌曲，经常在特殊的场合和体育赛事中使用。苏格兰没有正式的国歌，《蘇格蘭之花》是非正式履行这一职责的歌曲之一，其他歌曲还包括《{{le|苏格兰人 (歌曲)|Scots Wha Hae|苏格兰人}}》（Scots Wha Hae），《[[蘇格蘭勇士|蘇格蘭勇士]]》（Scotland the Brave） 和《[[高地大教堂|高地大教堂]]》（Highland Cathedral）<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/4828454.stm|title=Action call over national anthem|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=2006-03-21|accessdate=2011-11-30|archive-date=2009-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090606153053/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/4828454.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/3224209.stm|title=Scots anthem call rejected|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=2003-10-29|accessdate=2011-11-30|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202034917/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/3224209.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这首歌曲由{{le|罗伊·威廉森|Roy Williamson}}和他的组合The Corries创作，发表于1967年<ref>[http://www.corries.com/news.php The Corries website] {{Wayback|url=http://www.corries.com/news.php |date=20100829194041 }} - (visited 28 August 2007)</ref>。歌曲中提到了1314年由[[罗伯特·布鲁斯|罗伯特·布鲁斯]]领导的[[班诺克本之战|班诺克本之战]]的胜利，那次战争打败了[[英格兰王国|英格兰王国]]的[[爱德华二世_(英格兰)|爱德华二世]]，班诺克本战役是苏格兰与英格兰数百年交战史上，苏格兰最重要的一次全面胜利。

==歌词==
{| align="center" cellspacing="25px"
|'''[[低地苏格兰语|低地苏格兰语]]'''
<poem>
O Flouer o Scotland,
Whan will we see,
Yer like again,
That focht and dee'd for,
Yer wee bit Hill an Glenn,
An stuid agin him,
Prood Edward's Airmie,
An sent him hamewart,
Tae think again.

The Hills is bare nou,
An Autumn leafs,
Lies thick an still,
Ower land that is tint nou,
That thae sae darlie held,
That stuid agin him,
Prood Edward's Airmie,
An sent him hamewart,
Tae think again.

Thir days is past nou,
An in the past,
Thay mun remain,
But we can aye rise nou,
An be the naition again,
That stuid agin him,
Prood Edward's Airmie,
An sent him hamewart,
Tae think again.
</poem>

|'''[[英语|英语]]'''
<poem>
O Flower of Scotland, 
When will we see
Your like again,
That fought and died for,
Your wee bit Hill and Glen,
And stood against him,
Proud Edward's Army,
And sent him homeward,
To think again.

The Hills are bare now,
And Autumn leaves
lie thick and still,
O'er land that is lost now,
Which those so dearly held,
That stood against him,
Proud Edward's Army,
And sent him homeward,
To think again.

Those days are past now,
And in the past
they must remain,
But we can still rise now,
And be the nation again,
That stood against him,
Proud Edward's Army,
And sent him homeward,
To think again.
</poem>

|'''[[苏格兰盖尔语|苏格兰盖尔语]]'''
<poem>
O Fhlùir na h-Alba,
cuin a chì sinn
an seòrsa laoich
a sheas gu bàs 'son
am bileag feòir is fraoich,
a sheas an aghaidh
feachd uailleil Iomhair
's a ruaig e dhachaidh
air chaochladh smaoin?

Na cnuic tha lomnochd
 's tha duilleach Foghair
mar bhrat air làr,
am fearann caillte
dan tug na seòid ud gràdh,
a sheas an aghaidh
feachd uailleil Iomhair
's a ruaig e dhachaigh
air chaochladh smaoin.

Tha 'n eachdraidh dùinte
ach air dìochuimhne
chan fheum i bhith,
is faodaidh sinn èirigh
gu bhith nar Rìoghachd a-rìs
a sheas an aghaidh
feachd uailleil Iomhair
's a ruaig e dhachaidh
air chaochladh smaoin.
</poem>
